		<div id="comment_body_64357586">  I'm one of those annoying persons who by nature spot incongruities in text. AKA "Proofreader Syndrome."

 The title was surprising. I saw "can apps" as what is turning us. Well, nope! So, it was a giggle, but since the advent of nearly ubiquitous strange word usages, curiously disjointed sentences, and many similar errors I almost never saw pre-AI, I'm seeing many more of them. I understand, sure, AI is all A, little i. Gives me the willies, that. Makes the future a wee bit more scary.

